But may not Euſtathius be thought to derive it here rather from Homer him ſelfe? I think, not: for all that can be made of his words is not that Homer doth directly ſay ſo; but this, that the Poet doth adſcribe ſuch affections unto the Gods, as may be thought to proceed from ſuch a cauſe. Homer's owne words in that place are theſe;
〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 — That is, How have the Gods appointed unto miſerable men, to live in grief?
